gm prose externalization (string-externalization project): agent-facing phase instruction text + gate/residual messages live in an editable bundle at gm-plugkit/instructions/*.md, shipped by gm-plugkit and provisioned into .gm/instructions/<key>.md. rs-plugkit/src/prose.rs serves the bundle entry per key and falls back to the compiled const when the bundle file is absent -- so editing agent-facing prose is a gm-plugkit republish with NO Rust rebuild. The bundle .md files and the rs-plugkit src/orchestrator/instructions/<key>.rs consts are kept byte-aligned by gm-plugkit/scripts/sync-instruction-consts.mjs, which regenerates each <key>.rs as `pub const TEXT` from the corresponding .md. This is the mechanism behind 'editing prose is a gm-plugkit republish, no Rust rebuild'.